Normalization vs Standardization
1️.Normalization
Normalization scales data to a fixed range, usually 0 to 1.

Formula often used:

Normalized value=𝑥−min(𝑥)max⁡(𝑥)−min⁡(𝑥)
Useful when data does not follow a normal distribution.
Sensitive to outliers.
Example:If values are between 20 and 80, normalization converts them into 0–1 range.

Standardization
Standardization transforms data so it has:
.Mean = 0
.Standard deviation = 1

Formula:
𝑧=𝑥−𝜇/𝜎
Works well when data follows a normal (Gaussian) distribution.
Less affected by outliers compared to normalization.
Example:Converts values into Z‑scores (how many standard deviations away from the mean).

