1.Mean/Median Imputation
How it works:
.Replace missing “Age” values with the mean or median age of the column.

When to use:
.Mean → when data is normally distributed (no extreme outliers).
.Median → when data has outliers (e.g., a few very high ages).

2.Deleting Rows with Missing Age
How it works:
.Remove rows where the “Age” value is missing.

When to use:
.When the number of missing values is very small.
.When deleting them does not affect the dataset size or analysis.

