z‑score standardization is preferred when outliers exist because it is less sensitive to extreme values.
Min‑Max scaling gets heavily distorted by outliers since it depends on minimum and maximum values,
 while Z‑score maintains the overall distribution by scaling data based on mean and standard deviation.
